cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep neural network for non-rigid structure from motion (NRSfM) which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the proposed neural network is mathematically interpretable as a multi-layer block sparse dictionary learning problem, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a quality measure based on the network weights, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves 3D shape reconstruction, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
